            "commit": "c6b0d0e779c18809d1ef9a6e352349107c7e68d8",
            "subject": "LU-6261 gnilnd: Use kgnilnd_vzalloc to allocate fma blocks."
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Chris Horn",
          "email": "hornc@cray.com",
          "date": "2015-07-27 13:59:57.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-07-31 01:33:11.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-6261 gnilnd: kgnilnd_check_rdma_cq race in error path.",
        "message": "LU-6261 gnilnd: kgnilnd_check_rdma_cq race in error path.\n\nIt is possible for multiple threads to both be processing a\ntransaction error that causes the connection to close.\nIf the close path stalls after changing the conn state to CLOSING,\nthe tx_done path will put a tx in purgatory since the conn state is\nnot ESTABLISHED anymore. When the close path continues, it expects to\nfind that the conn->gnc_mdd_list is empty and assert if it isn't\nempty.\nChange the error code for the tx_done path so that we don't put this\ntx in purgatory since we are closing the connection anyway.\n\nSigned-off-by: Chris Horn <hornc@cray.com>\nChange-Id: I4458522f16508eb53d380f62320c65c7bf84657a\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/15439\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: James Shimek <jshimek@cray.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\nReviewed-by: Doug Oucharek <doug.s.oucharek@intel.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
